      • addLines

        void addLines(java.lang.String line,
              java.io.BufferedReader br)
       throws java.io.IOException
        Adds lines to validLines, deadlockOrLines, and arrowOrLines depending on the logical statement that the user has inputed. Lines that fit the statement will be put into the above ArrayLists while invalid lines will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        line - File line that is parsed against the logic statement
        br - Buffered Reader to read through the file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • addORs

        void addORs()
        Looks at the logical statement that the user has given and checks for special cases (such as AND NOT DEADLOCK, AND NOT arrow and sees if an OR operand was set. If so, then the variable orWord is set as the corresponding word.

      • progressArrowBr

        java.lang.String progressArrowBr(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                 java.lang.String line)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        Progresses the buffered reader if the user has indicated that they do not want to include any arrow errors. If there is a single arrow (indicated by a time stamp difference) then the function will return the line right below the first arrow found. Otherwise if there are matching arrows, the line returned will be the line below the matching arrow.
        Parameters:
        logbr - A buffered reader to advance through the file, same br from LogParser
        line - The file line where an arrow was found
        Returns:
        Returns a string that gives the program a new place to parse through
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • progressDeadlockBr

        java.lang.String progressDeadlockBr(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                    java.lang.String line)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Progresses the buffered reader if the user has indicated that they do not want to include any DEADLOCK errors. If there is a single DEADLOCK (indicated by a time stamp dif) then the function will return the line right below the first DEADLOCK found. Otherwise if there are matching DEADLOCKs, the line returned will be the line below the matching DEADLOCK.
        Parameters:
        logbr - A buffered reader to advance through the file, same br from LogParser
        line - File line where a DEADLOCK was found
        Returns:
        Returns a string that gives the program a new place to parse through
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • makeDeadlockLine

        java.lang.String makeDeadlockLine(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                                  java.lang.String line)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Generates a string that returns the entire deadlock error, which includes the first line where a deadlock was found, and then the subsequent lines in between the matching deadlock. If the error is a single error occurrence, then the error message is simply "".
        Parameters:
        logbr - Buffered Reader to read through file, same br from LogParser
        line - File line where DEADLOCK first occurred
        Returns:
        Returns a string with the full DEADLOCK error
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • makeArrowLine

        java.lang.String makeArrowLine(java.io.BufferedReader logbr,
                               java.lang.String logLine)
                        throws java.io.IOException
        Generates the entire line of an arrow error, and includes all the lines between the first arrow and then the matching arrow error. The string returned includes the first line where the arrow was found and the full error message, but not the line including the matching arrow. If there is only a single arrow, then only the first line is returned.
        Parameters:
        logbr - Buffered Reader to read through file, same br from LogParser
        logLine - File line where an arrow was first found
        Returns:
        Returns a string with the full arrow error, null if outside time stamp bounds user chose in the interface
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
